 <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">After controlling for safety-specific transformational leadership, we found that as predicted, learning goal orientation was positively related to near-miss recognition (β = 0.04, 
  <span class="italic">p</span> &lt; 0.01, 
  <a rid="T2" ref-type="table" href="#T2">Table 2</a>). A Monte Carlo based simulation (20,000 repetitions; 
  <a rid="B51" ref-type="bibr" href="#B51">Selig and Preacher, 2008</a>) revealed that safety-specific transformational leadership enhanced near-miss recognition by stimulating employees’ learning goal orientation (β = 0.04, 
  <span class="italic">p</span> &lt; 0.01, CI [0.013, 0.068], 
  <a rid="T2" ref-type="table" href="#T2">Table 2</a>), and that safety-specific active transactional leadership positively influenced near-miss recognition by stimulating performance goal orientation (β = 0.04, 
  <span class="italic">p</span> &lt; 0.01, CI [0.020, 0.074], 
  <a rid="T2" ref-type="table" href="#T2">Table 2</a>). All confidence intervals excluded zero. Thus we found support for Hypotheses 1c and 2c.
 </p>
